		<h2>Alessi Paint Palette</h2>
		<p>The Alessi Palette is a paint palette designed for Alessi after studying the works of a Italian industrial designer, Giulio Iacchetti. The palette combines aspects from two differentiating cultures, Italy and China, to represent the Italian Compnay Alessi and the fading culture in Vancouver Chinatown.</p>

		<h3>My Role</h3>
		<p>The Alessi Paint Palette was a project completed in two weeks. In the first week, my team and I researched about Alessi and the designer Giulio Iacchetti for inspirations. On the second week, along with designing and ideating the Palette with the group, I was in charge of the physical and digital (3D modeling) production of the project.</p>




