		<h2>Concept and Form</h2>
		<p>
		The palette was inspired from the reformation of Vancouver's Chinatown where many of it's buildings that brought the foundation of Chinese heritage and culture to Vancouver is slowly being replaced.</p>

		<a href="img/palette/facade.jpg" data-lightbox="palette" data-title="">
			<img class="project-pictures" src="img/palette/facade.jpg" alt="palette">
		</a>

		<p>The form of the paint palette was derived from the facade of the Green Buildling, one of the first and last remaining building still within Vancouver Chinatown. At the back of the palette is a triangular stand that represents the Green Building's inverted window while also providing comfort while holding the palette</p>

		<a href="img/palette/2.jpg" data-lightbox="palette" data-title="">
			<img class="project-pictures" src="img/palette/2.jpg" alt="palette">
		</a>


		<h2>Usage and Experience</h2>
		<p>
		We want our product to tell a story and the design of the palette replicates the story of Vancouver Chinatown. As paint is being used on the palette, it represents all the occurences and history that happened there. Once completed, the washing off of the palette represents the reformation of Chinatown, erasing away all the culture and history that was once an integral part of it's residence.</p>

